main event: Sighting of a star-like object from Ocean Station Victor on June 1, 1961.
interesting points: The object was brighter than a star and appeared to move across the sky at a speed of 15 knots., The sighting lasted for 2-3 minutes., The object was tracked across the sky with specific bearings and altitude noted., The coordinates of the ship's position were detailed in the report., The conclusion of the report suggested it was likely a satellite.
witness description: sighted by crew members aboard a ship at sea
